Software Engineer&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   Location: Saint Louis, USA   Job DescriptionPierianDx, a leader in the clinical genomics space, is currently seeking talented and motivated software engineers. As a Software Engineer, your duties will primarily revolve around building software by writing good quality code, as well as modifying software to fix errors, adapt it to new scenarios / requirements, improve its performance, or upgrade interfaces. You will also be involved in directing system testing and validation procedures, and also working with the customer success department on technical issues including software system design and maintenance.&amp;nbsp;To be successful in this role, you will need extensive knowledge of programming languages, problem solving skills, knowledge of best practices and the software development life-cycle.   About PierianDxEvery year millions of people bet their lives on precision medicine. PierianDx is on a mission to make sure that bet pays off. At PierianDx we empower progressive health institutions and diagnostic laboratories to build world-class precision medicine programs. Our industry-leading molecular genomics technologies and expertise deliver the most integrated, trusted, and collaborative approach across the clinical care spectrum. From genomic sequencing and biomedical informatics in the laboratory to reporting and decision support at the patient’s bedside, we drive the adoption of genomics in clinical care and accelerate the fight against cancer and other diseases. For more information, visit www.pieriandx.com   Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;  - Work with product teams to understand product requirements / user needs; ask relevant questions to get clarity on how the end user is going to use the system and understand acceptance criteria.   
  - Take ownership of developing end-to-end product features/epics/user stories&amp;nbsp;   
  - Contribute in design activities and documentation; Getting design reviewed by technical leads / architects; provide estimates for stories in the scope   
  - Develop “good quality code” using published best practices&amp;nbsp;   
  - Work as part of team to achieve sprint and release goals   
  - Participate in daily scrum to provide a plan for upcoming tasks and ask for help for any roadblocks, Keep the JIRA board updated.   
  - Work with Leads in creating documentation deliverables at each stage&amp;nbsp;   
  - Share knowledge with fellow teammates to improve their knowledge or skills   
  - Help customer success teams on technical issues including software system design and maintenance.   
  - Ensure compliance with SDLC processes defined at organization level to meet quality goals set at product level   
  - Stay up-to-date on product and process trainings required to create quality deliverables at each phase of product life-cycle   
&amp;nbsp;Required Skills and Experience&amp;nbsp;  - Must have experience with Node JS, React, Javascript, MongoDB, Basic Linux, and Basic Shell Scripting&amp;nbsp;   
  - Should be an outstanding programmer with minimum 2 years of experience in MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node JS) technology stack.   
  - Strong computer science fundamentals (OO programming, algorithms, data structures, databases).&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with continuous integration infrastructure for software development such as Jenkins.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with the structure and usage of REST API's&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience in Agile processes and comfortable with quick iterations.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Good communication (written and verbal) skills&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with SQL and No-SQL Databases&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with Docker   
  - Total years of experience: 2 to 5 years.   
   Preferred Experience  - Knowledge of JavaScript Frameworks (Angular, Vue) Elastic Search, Life sciences domain,&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with ECS/EKR/Docker Swarm/Kubernetes exposure   
  - Experience using Test Driven Development processes&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience working with FrontEnd Technologies (HTML, CSS, Javascript)&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with Java and Spring Boot technologies   
  - Full-Stack Software Development experience in both front end and back end technologies.&amp;nbsp;   
   EducationBachelor or Master of Science degree in Computer Science or equivalent from a reputed college.&amp;nbsp;   PierianDx is an Equal Opportunity EmployerPierianDx is a proud to be an equal opportunity employer committed to providing employment opportunity regardless of sex, race, creed, color, gender, religion, marital status, domestic partner status, age, national origin or ancestry, physical or mental disability, medical condition, sexual orientation, pregnancy, military or veteran status, citizenship status, and genetic information.&amp;nbsp;Work VerificationPierianDx verifies all employees for the right to work within the United States. To do this we participate in the E-verify program. This means that we provide the Social Security Administration (SSA) and, if necessary, the Department of Homeland Security (DHS), with information from each new employee’s Form I-9 to confirm work authorization.
